document_data.History:
After the disappearance of the Royal Magician [[Ganrahast]] and his second in command [[Vainrence]], Rorstil Hallowdant rebuked the Master of Revels, [[Khaladan Mallowfaer]], for a perceived excess from his own authority. Curiously, most seemed to agree with him there.{{cite book/Elminster Must Die/MMP|347-349|33}}

In the day of the [[Council of the Dragon]], Hallowdant had to excuse himself with some intestinal distress, forcing him to delegate the checking of the [[Castle Obarskyr/Hall of Justice|Hall of Justice]] to Corleth Fentable, his understeward, who had poisoned him.{{cite book/Bury Elminster Deep|29|3}} He was abed and snoring when the understeward left the palace, later, after the Council was finally held.{{cite book/Bury Elminster Deep|158|17}}

He was found dead later at [[Staghaven House]] alongside all its inhabitants, his body cursed so that anyone who tried to pry information out of it was struck down with insanity.
